{"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"roleHeading":"WWDC24","role":"sampleCode","title":"Discover RealityKit APIs for iOS, macOS and visionOS"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc24-10103-discover-realitykit-apis-for-ios-macos-and-visionos"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC24-10103-Discover-RealityKit-APIs-for-iOS-macOS-and-visionOS","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"article","sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC24"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how new cross-platform APIs in RealityKit can help you build immersive apps for iOS, macOS, and visionOS. Check out the new hover effects, lights and shadows, and portal crossing features, and view them in action through real examples."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Key-Takeaways","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Key Takeaways"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"üñ•Ô∏è Feature parity on visionOS, iOS, iPadOS & macOS"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"üí° Lights on visionOS","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"üîò New hover effect styles: highlight & shader"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"üëã Hand tracking via AnchorEntities for hand joints","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"üß≤ Force effects"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"‚õìÔ∏è‚Äçüí• Physics joints"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"üßø Portal enhancements"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"üëÅÔ∏è BillboardComponent"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ü™© Subdivision surface & much more"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"columns":[{"size":1,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC24-10103-Overview1"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"size":1,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC24-10103-Overview2","type":"image"}]}]}],"numberOfColumns":2,"type":"row"},{"columns":[{"size":1,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC24-10103-Overview3"}]}]},{"size":1,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC24-10103-Overview4"}]}]}],"numberOfColumns":2,"type":"row"},{"anchor":"Sample-game","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Sample game"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The presenter, Yidi Zhu, a RealityKit engineer, showcases the new features of RealityKit by creating a toy spaceship game in this session. The game is extended in the session ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC24-111801-Enhance-your-spatial-computing-app-with-RealityKit-audio","type":"reference"},{"text":" and the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/RealityKit\/creating-a-spaceship-game","type":"reference"},{"text":" is available online.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"New-features-not-covered-in-detail","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"New features not covered in detail"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The following new capabilities of RealityKit are just briefly mentioned in this session, the viewer is referred to the documentation:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Low-level access to meshes and textures via "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"LowLevelMesh","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"LowLevelTexture"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"New animation system capabilities, such as "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"animation timelines"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" in Reality Composer Pro."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"BillboardComponent","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"text","text":" introduces a privacy-preserving way to make entities always face the user."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"PixelCast"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" enables pixel-perfect entity selection through a rendering-based approach.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Subdivision surface","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" enables smooth surfaces rendering without creating a dense mesh.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Cross-platform-capabilities","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Cross-platform capabilities"},{"columns":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"RealityKit has achieved "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"feature parity"}]},{"type":"text","text":" on all platforms (except tvOS): visionOS, iOS, iPadOS and macOS. But there are differences to consider, when developing a cross-platform app:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"table","header":"row","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"visionOS","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"iOS, iPadOS, macOS"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Spatial UI layout","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"2D UI layout"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"ImmersiveSpace","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"RealityView"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Hands-based input"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Touch-based input","type":"text"}]}]]]}],"size":3},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC24-10103-APIs"}]}],"size":2}],"numberOfColumns":5,"type":"row"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To this end, ","type":"text"},{"code":"RealityView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" has received some enhancements like ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"camera mode"}]},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"post processing"}]},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The camera mode can be set to world tracking like this:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["RealityView { content in","#if os(iOS)","    content.camera = .worldTracking","#endif","}"]}],"style":"tip","type":"aside","name":"Tip"},{"anchor":"Dynamic-lights","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Dynamic lights"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"RealityKit‚Äôs three types of lights are now available in visionOS 2.0 (author‚Äôs comment: Finally! üéâ).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"However, only spot and directional lights can cast shadows (author‚Äôs comment: üò≠).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC24-10103-Lights"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Here‚Äôs how to add a spotlight to a spaceship‚Äôs ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Headlight"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" entity:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["guard let lightEntity = spaceship.findEntity(named: \"HeadLight\") else { return }","lightEntity.components.set(SpotLightComponent(color: .yellow, intensity: 10000.0, attenuationRadius: 6.0))","lightEntity.components.set(SpotLightComponent.Shadow())"],"type":"codeListing"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you don‚Äôt want an entity to cast a shadow, use this code:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let component = DynamicLightShadowComponent(castsShadow: false)","entity.components.set(component)"],"syntax":"swift"}],"style":"tip","type":"aside","name":"Tip"},{"anchor":"Hover-effects","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Hover effects"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"HoverEffectComponent"},{"type":"text","text":" has two new styles, in addition to the default "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spotlight"},{"type":"text","text":" style:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Highlight"}]},{"type":"text","text":": The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"highlight"},{"type":"text","text":" style applies a uniform highlight to the entire mesh. Its tint color and strength can be modified, which is now also possible for the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spotlight"},{"type":"text","text":" style:"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let highlightStyle = HoverEffectComponent.HighlightHoverEffectStyle(color: .lightYellow, strength: 0.8)","let hoverEffect = HoverEffectComponent(.highlight(highlightStyle))","spaceship.components.set(hoverEffect)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Shader","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": The shader style integrates with a shader graph material created with Reality Composer Pro, using the HoverState node‚Äôs intensity value:","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"columns":[{"size":2,"content":[{"type":"codeListing","code":["let hoverEffect = HoverEffectComponent(.shader(.default))","spaceship.components.set(hoverEffect)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A more complex example is developed in the session "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC24-10104-Build-a-spatial-drawing-app-with-RealityKit"}]}]},{"size":1,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC24-10103-HoverStateNode"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"numberOfColumns":3,"type":"row"},{"anchor":"Hand-tracking","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Hand tracking"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Spatial Tracking API makes custom hand tracking easier, which was previously possibly through ARKit only:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use a "},{"code":"SpatialTrackingSession","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to get the user‚Äôs consent for hand tracking."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AnchorEntity"},{"type":"text","text":" for a joint like this:"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC24-10103-HandTracking"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here‚Äôs how to control a spaceship‚Äôs acceleration via the distance between left thumb and index finger, in a system‚Äôs update function:"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["class HandTrackingSystem: System {","    func update(context: SceneUpdateContext) {","        let indexTipPosition = indexTipEntity.position(relativeTo: nil)","        let thumbTipPosition = thumbTipEntity.position(relativeTo: nil)","        let distance = distance(indexTipPosition, thumbTipPosition)","        let force = spaceship.transform.forward * computeThrottle(with: distance)","        spaceship.addForce(force, relativeTo: nil)","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Another example is developed in the session "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC24-10104-Build-a-spatial-drawing-app-with-RealityKit"}]},{"anchor":"Force-effects","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Force effects"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There are 4 built-in force effects, that define a volume and continuously apply forces to physics bodies in that volume:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Constant radial"}]},{"type":"text","text":" applies a constant force towards the center"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Vortex"}]},{"type":"text","text":" applies forces that circulate bodies around the axis"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Drag","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" applies a breaking force proportional to the velocity"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Turbulence"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" applies random forces","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC24-10103-ForceEffects"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Custom"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" force effects can be defined by setting ","type":"text"},{"code":"parameterTypes","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"forceMode","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", and an ","type":"text"},{"code":"update","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function of a ","type":"text"},{"code":"ForceEffectProtocol","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", like this gravity effect:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["struct Gravity: ForceEffectProtocol {","    var parameterTypes: PhysicsBodyParameterTypes { [.position, .distance] }","    var forceMode: ForceMode = .force","","    func update(parameters: inout ForceEffectParameters) {","        guard let distances = parameters.distances,","              let positions = parameters.positions else { return }","","        for i in 0..<parameters.physicsBodyCount {","            let force = computeForce(distances[i], positions[i])","            parameters.setForce(force, index: i)","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Custom force effects can be activated like this:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let gravity = ForceEffect(effect: Gravity(),","                          spatialFalloff: SpatialForceFalloff(bounds: .sphere(radius: 8.0)),","                          mask: .asteroids)","planet.components.set(ForceEffectComponent(effects: [gravity]))"],"type":"codeListing"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To apply an initial velocity to an entity, use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PhysicsMotionComponent"},{"type":"text","text":" like this:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let physicsMotion = PhysicsMotionComponent(linearVelocity: initialVelocity)","asteroid.components.set(physicsMotion)"]}],"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note"},{"anchor":"Physics-joints","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Physics joints"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Joints connect two pins of two physics bodies together through constraints regarding translation and\/or rotation. Pins define a position and orientation that‚Äôs relative to the entity. There are 6 types of joints:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed: Disallows translation and rotation."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Spherical: Prevents translation, allows limited Y\/Z axis rotation and free rotation around the X-axis.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Revolute: Prevents translation, allows only rotation around the X-axis.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Prismatic (also called slide joint): Only allows translation along the X-axis.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Distance: Allows free movement as long as the distance between the two bodies is within a given range."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Custom","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC24-10103-Joints"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Here‚Äôs how to set a custom joint between a spaceship (where the pin is at the position of a ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Hook"}]},{"text":" entity) and its trailer:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["guard let hookEntity = spaceship.findEntity(named: \"Hook\") else { return }","let hookOffset: SIMD3<Float> = hookEntity.position(relativeTo: spaceship)","let hookPin = spaceship.pins.set(named: \"Hook\", position: hookOffset)","let trailerPin = trailer.pins.set(named: \"Trailer\", position: .zero)","var joint = PhysicsCustomJoint(pin0: hookPin, pin1: trailerPin)","joint.angularMotionAroundX = .range(-.pi * 0.05 ... .pi * 0.05)","joint.angularMotionAroundY = .range(-.pi * 0.2 ... .pi * 0.2)","joint.angularMotionAroundZ = .range(-.pi * 0.2 ... .pi * 0.2)","joint.linearMotionAlongX = .fixed","joint.linearMotionAlongY = .fixed","joint.linearMotionAlongZ = .fixed","try joint.addToSimulation()"],"type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Portal-enhancements","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Portal enhancements"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here‚Äôs how to let an object smoothly cross a portal‚Äôs surface:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["portal.components.set(PortalComponent(target: portalWorld, ","\t\t\t\t     clippingMode: .plane(.positiveZ), ","\t\t\t\t     crossingMode: .plane(.positiveZ)))","spaceship.components.set(PortalCrossingComponent())"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC24-10103-PortalCrossing","type":"image"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Since the lighting conditions inside and outside of the portal may differ, a harsh lighting change might occur. To avoid it, use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EnvironmentLightingConfigurationComponent"},{"text":" like this:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["var lightingConfig = EnvironmentLightingConfigurationComponent()","let distance: Float = computeShipDistanceFromPortal()","lightingConfig.environmentLightingWeight = mapDistanceToWeight(distance)","spaceship.components.set(lightingConfig)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Written-By","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Written By"},{"columns":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"VielfaltSoftware"}]}],"size":1},{"content":[{"text":"Alexander Gross","level":3,"anchor":"Alexander-Gross","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"overridingTitle":"Contributed Notes","type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/VielfaltSoftware","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Contributed Notes","type":"text"}]},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"|","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/VielfaltSoftware"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"|","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/x.com\/VielfaltApps"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"|","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/vielfalt.software"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"size":4}],"numberOfColumns":5,"type":"row"},{"type":"thematicBreak"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Missin